      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The safest bet is always to lean toward the most conventional, conservative standards that the majority of the board members are accustomed to. For hair, styles that are tightly controlled and neatly managed, whether straightened or in a very sleek, contained natural style, tend to be perceived as most corporate. Regarding accessories, keeping them minimal and subtle ensures they don't draw undue attention away from the substance of the discussion. When in doubt, aim for the most traditional, understated look.",
